SIMPLE: wholly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wholly
<hw>Whol"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a
whole or complete manner; entirely; completely; perfectly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor <qex>wholly</qex> overcome, nor <qex>wholly</qex> yield.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To the exclusion of other things; totally;
fully.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They employed themselves <qex>wholly</qex> in domestic life.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whom</ent>⟦br⟧
